[1] Philippines
Date: Thu 6 Sep 2018
Source: Inquirer Southern Luzon [edited]
http://newsinfo.inquirer.net/1028991/doh-3-dead-as-measles-hit-bicol-region


At least 3 patients in the provinces of Albay and Camarines Norte have died from measles, with almost 200 more suspected cases in the Bicol region, the Department of Health (DOH) said Thu [6 Sep 2018]. Dr. Rita Mae Ang-Bon, the family cluster head of DOH Bicol, said they have recorded 187 suspected cases of measles throughout the region from 1 Jan to 1 Sep this year [2018]. "[The number of cases] is high compared [with] 2017 covering the same period, which only reached up to 54 suspected cases," Bon said.

The DOH has recorded 12 measles cases in Albay, 38 in Camarines Norte, 60 in Camarines Sur, 3 in Catanduanes, 62 in Masbate, and 12 in Sorsogon. Meanwhile, simultaneous school-based measles, mumps and rubella vaccinations were done by the DOH nationwide to protect students from the diseases.

[Byline: Michael Jaucian]

