[3] Texas (Houston)
Date: Wed 5 Sep 2018
Source: Houston Public Media [edited]
https://www.houstonpublicmedia.org/articles/news/health-science/2018/09/05/302903/cdc-confirms-measles-case-in-houston


The Centers for Disease Control and Prevention (CDC) confirmed Wed [5 Sep 2018] a case of measles in Houston, according to the City's Health Department. The Health Department detailed that a young boy, between the age of 1 and 3 years, contracted the illness. The boy was being treated at Texas Children's Hospital.

This is the 1st case of measles in Houston since 2013. The Health Department has found that, so far, no other persons who could have been exposed are at risk of having contracted the illness.

Houston has averaged fewer than one reported case of measles each year over the past decade. [...]

[Byline: Al Ortiz]

