[4] Texas: Southwest Airlines alert
Date: Fri 7 Sep 2018 
Source: Time [edited]
http://time.com/5389992/texas-flights-measles/


A Texas resident sick with measles may have exposed passengers on 4 Southwest Airlines flights to the highly contagious virus, officials said. The individual took flights connecting through Houston's Hobby Airport on 21 and 22 Aug 2018, the Houston Health Department announced Thursday [6 Sep 2018].

The passenger was diagnosed with measles after traveling, a Southwest representative told TIME, but health department said the person was contagious at the time of the flights. Southwest Airlines is working with the Centers for Disease Control and Prevention (CDC) to notify passengers on 4 flights of the possible exposure, the airline said [see source URL above for specifics of the flights].

Widespread and effective vaccination has made measles rare in the United States, but 107 cases across 21 states were reported during the first 6 months of this year [2018] alone, in part because of lingering antivaccine sentiment. [...]

[Byline: Jamie Ducharme]

